import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

global input_len
global forecast_horizon
input_len=24
forecast_horizon=48

def getTrainTestData():
    data=pd.read_csv("gas_price.csv")

    split_point=input_len+forecast_horizon-1

    data.set_index("dt",inplace=True)
    
    #normalize by train datas min max values
    max=data.iloc[:-split_point].max()[0]
    min=data.iloc[:-split_point].min()[0]
    data=(data-min)/(max-min)

    x=[]
    y=[]
    for i in range(input_len, len(data.index)):
        x.append(np.array(data.iloc[i-input_len:i]))
        y.append(np.array(data.iloc[i]))

    xTrain=x[:-forecast_horizon]
    yTrain=y[:-forecast_horizon]
    xTest=x[-forecast_horizon:]
    yTest=y[-forecast_horizon:]

    #reshape data to keras format (batch_size, timesteps, data_dim)
    xTrain=np.array(xTrain)
    xTrain=xTrain.reshape(xTrain.shape[0],input_len,1)
    yTrain=np.array(yTrain)
    yTrain=yTrain.reshape(yTrain.shape[0],1,1)
    xTest=np.array(xTest)
    xTest=xTest.reshape(xTest.shape[0],input_len,1)
    yTest=np.array(data.iloc[-forecast_horizon:])
    yTest=yTest.reshape(forecast_horizon,1,1)

    #rescale df
    data=(data*(max-min))+min

    return data,xTrain,xTest,yTrain,yTest,min,max

#get data
df,xTrain,xTest,yTrain,yTest,min,max=getTrainTestData()
# create model
from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping
from keras.layers import LSTM,Dense,GRU

enco_deco = Sequential()

enco_deco.add(Dense(units=1))

enco_deco.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mse')

enco_deco.summary()
